# Manga Extractor (MEextension) - Project Overview

## What This Project Is

A manga/comic page extractor that downloads images from Japanese online manga reader websites and packages them into ZIP files. Supports multiple reader platforms.

## Architecture: CLI-First + Optional Chrome Extension

The project has TWO delivery mechanisms for the same handler code:

1. **CLI tool** (`cli/extract.ts`) -- Puppeteer-based, runs from terminal, fully automatable
2. **Chrome extension** (`chrome/manifest.json`) -- Overlay UI, manual use in the browser

Both use the same handler scripts from `app/handlers/`.

### Handler Types

| Type | Handlers | How they work | CLI path |
|------|----------|---------------|----------|
| API-based | takecomic, nico-douga, comic-walker | HTTP requests + optional descrambling | Puppeteer navigates to page, injects handler script |
| DOM-based | speed-binb, kindle, comicbushi, comic-pixiv | DOM access + dom-to-image capture | Puppeteer navigates to page, injects handler script |

All handlers are built as IIFE bundles that auto-execute `main()` when injected.

### Tool Roles

- **Shell**: runs build, extract, verify commands
- **Cursor browser**: explores manga sites (DOM, network, screenshots) + sanity checks extracted output vs live site
- **Puppeteer** (via Shell): drives a real Chrome to execute handlers on actual pages

## Directory Structure

```
cli/                          # CLI extraction + verification tools
  extract.ts                  # Main entry: bun cli/extract.ts --reader X --url URL
  puppeteer-runner.ts         # Shared Puppeteer launcher
  verify.ts                   # Sanity checks + viewer.html generator

app/handlers/                 # Site-specific extraction handlers (shared by CLI + extension)
  _template.ts                # Scaffold for new handlers
  NOTES.md                    # Per-handler status, issues, findings
  takecomic.ts                # Takecomic/Comici reader (API-based)
  speed-binb-reader.js        # Speed Binb reader (DOM-based)
  comic-walker.js             # Comic Walker / Nico Douga (API-based)
  nico-douga.js               # Nico Douga (API-based)
  comic-pixiv.js              # Comic Pixiv (DOM-based)
  kindle.js                   # Kindle Cloud Reader (DOM-based)
  comicbushi.js               # Comicbushi (DOM-based, CORS issues)

app/utils/                    # Shared utilities (zipAndDownload, timeout, etc.)
src/                          # Chrome extension TypeScript source (React UI, background, content script)
static/                       # Static assets (HTML, CSS, fonts)
chrome/                       # Chrome extension manifest + icons
build/                        # Build output (extension + handler IIFE bundles)
build.ts                      # Bun build script
```

## Key Commands

```bash
bun run build                  # Build extension + handlers
bun run dev                    # Build with file watching
bun cli/extract.ts --reader takecomic --url "..." --out ./output   # Extract
bun cli/verify.ts --input ./output                                  # Verify
bun run lint                   # ESLint
bun run format                 # Prettier
```

## Conventions

- Handlers export `main()` and all helper functions for testability
- Handlers end with `main();` which auto-executes in IIFE builds
- Handler files starting with `_` are templates/scaffolds and not built
- All handler types/functions use `export` keyword
- TypeScript for new code; legacy JS handlers are gradually migrated
- Build target: ES2022, browser context

## MANDATORY: NOTES.md Protocol

**Read `app/handlers/NOTES.md` at the START of every session** that involves handlers, extraction, or site exploration.

**Update `app/handlers/NOTES.md` at the END of every session** -- even if you only ran a test or explored a site without code changes. This is not optional. Record:
- Test URLs with real values (not placeholders)
- Bugs found and fixes applied
- Site quirks discovered (CSP, auth, DOM structure, API endpoints)
- What was tried and failed
- Updated `Last tested` date

Future agents depend entirely on NOTES.md to avoid repeating mistakes and wasting time. If you skip this, the next agent will hit the same problems you already solved.
